
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes from the [.arguments] node to the [where] node within a [data.read] structure. The [get-nodes] slot retrieves all nodes under [.arguments], and these nodes are then added to the [where] node, allowing dynamic modification of query conditions based on input arguments. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified destination node.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the specified source node.
 */
add:x:./*/data.read/*/where/*
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
